    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-05-31T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-05-31T08:00:00-05:00" n="452"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d452">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">859B.01/191: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Godthaab</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Penfield</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Godthaab</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-31T10:00:00-03:00"
                            >May 31, 1940—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 9 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>18. Department’s No. 12, May 29, paragraph 2.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Svane approves of the Department’s proposal. It is respectfully suggested
                        that I be authorized to accompany Svane to Ivigtut on the <hi rend="italic"
                            >Campbell</hi>.</item>
                    <pb facs="0377" n="368" xml:id="pg_368"/>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Although Svane has yet made no requests in connection with the transaction
                        he is, judging from his remarks, considering <hi rend="italic">inter
                            alia</hi> the following questions: (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) would it
                        be possible to return to the United States Government small arms in excess
                        of those needed for a guard of not more than 20 persons, the cost price to
                        be refunded or applied as part payment for another 3-inch gun to be mounted
                        on the point just west of the mine property; and (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>)
                        would it be possible to resell the equipment to the American Government at a
                        reduced figure after the war. I have told him that I am sure that the
                        American Government will adopt a fair and reasonable attitude regarding this
                        matter.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Penfield</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
